<item>
            <title>[SPARK-27248] REFRESH TABLE should recreate cache with same cache name and storage level</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-27248</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;If we refresh a cached table, the table cache will be first uncached and then recache (lazily). Currently, the logic is embedded in CatalogImpl.refreshTable method.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;The current implementation does not preserve&#160;the cache name and storage level. As a result, cache name and cache level could be changed after a REFERSH. IMHO, it is not what a user would expect.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I would like to fix this behavior by first save the cache name and storage level for recaching the table.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
